<font color="#FF0000">CONTROL AND FEAR</font><br>
<tt>Tue Sep 23 23:43:39 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
At the bottom of every fear lies the haunting thought..&quot;Will I be controlled or in control or out of control.&quot;<br><br>
At the bottom of every emotion there is a fear base.<br><br>
Having been controlled badly in the past by others or circumstance or both... I will NOT let it happen again... I will not trust as readily or will not trust at all.<br><br>
If I isolate.. my world becomes very small.. and easier for me to control everything... but it is a lonely place... where I don't find acceptance from others, which is the true purpose of having control in the first place.<br><br>
If I am adamate enough my will (controls) shall prevail at all times.. of course the foreman and the wife and the kids and the neighbors and everyone will view my interpersonal relationships skills as horrible and view me as unacceptable and I will ultimately lose the greatest control of all... finding acceptance (the greatest pleasure.) But, I can always turn to veterans, most of whom will accept me no matter what!<br><br>
If I lie to myself, when I need to... then I have control.  Of course, some one is always waiting to point out the fact that I am wrong and not dealing with reality.  I can scream at them or kick the shit out of them and regain control, but I end up alienating myself.. loosing acceptance and that is what I really want to control is being accepted instead of rejected.<br><br>
All I really want is to have pleasure and avoid pain, be accepted and not rejected, feel secure instead of insecure. How do I control all of that.. or can I...or should I?<br><br>
If I could control everything... I would never be unhappy again.. If I could control everything... I would have nothing to fear!<br><br>
Mustang Two Four
